<plot>Set against the backdrop of New York City as it was still reeling in the wake of September 11 while the war in Iraq was spiraling out of control half a world away, "Every Dog's Day" is at once a loving tribute to and stinging satire of the persistence of petty money squabbles and affairs of the heart in dire times, and a tragically funny reminder that some people never learn.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?184185</url></doc>
